jack-in-the-box-los-angeles-516-n-beaudr.name: Jack in the Box
jack-in-the-box-los-angeles-516-n-beaudr.description: Burgers, fries, tacos, breakfast, pure culinary bliss—is there anything you can't get at Jack in the Box? With delicious menu options any time of day, this chain does the classics right while thinking outside of the box for new treats to try. From inventive breakfast offerings to trendy shake flavors, you're sure to find something to tickle your tastebuds at Jack in the Box. No time for a trip to pick up your square meal? Let Postmates bring it to you, so you can focus on savoring every single bite. Hop online or in our app to get your Jack in the Box favorites ASAP.

Tiny Tacos.name: Tiny Tacos
Tiny Tacos.description: *Please read the following in a movie trailer voice* In a world...where tacos have always been the same size, one food will change the course of history - Tiny Tacos! This winter, experience the biggest little blockbuster of the year, 15 Tiny Tacos and an all-new Creamy Avocado Lime dipping sauce.  *End movie trailer voice, if you want.*

Loaded Tiny Tacos.description: *Please read the following in a movie trailer voice* In a world...where tacos have always been the same size, one food will change the course of history - Loaded Tiny Tacos! Breakfast Jack.name: Breakfast Jack
Breakfast Jack.description: The name speaks for itself. This is breakfast, Jack-style. Think ham, a freshly cracked egg, and American cheese—all on a bun. Now, try to think of something else. That’s right. You can’t.

Jumbo Breakfast Platter.name: Jumbo Breakfast Platter
Jumbo Breakfast Platter.description: Breakfast doesn’t come shaped in a bar. Or in a fancy juice. Real breakfast is served on a platter—a jumbo platter with tasty scrambled eggs, hash browns, eight mini pancakes, and your choice of country grilled sausage or three slices of bacon. Checkmate, fancy juice.

Ultimate Breakfast Sandwich.name: Ultimate Breakfast Sandwich
Ultimate Breakfast Sandwich.description: So, ultimate, huh? Are two freshly cracked eggs ultimate? Maybe. Two slices of American cheese? Possibly. How about two slices of ham and bacon? Potentially. Okay, then what about all of the above on a buttery bakery bun? Oh, yes. Definitely. That’s textbook ultimate. That’s a textbook you want to eat.

Extreme Sausage Sandwich.name: Extreme Sausage Sandwich
Extreme Sausage Sandwich.description: When Jack put a sausage patty, American cheese and a freshly cracked egg on a buttery bakery bun, people went nuts. And then when Jack doubled the sausage and cheese, search parties were organized. Because people lost their minds.

Loaded Breakfast Sandwich.name: Loaded Breakfast Sandwich
Loaded Breakfast Sandwich.description: When a breakfast sandwich has freshly cracked eggs, hickory smoked bacon, ham, sausage, melted American cheese, and toasted sourdough bread, it’s just not a breakfast sandwich—it’s the Loaded Breakfast Sandwich. Which means you wouldn’t need to eat anything else. Maybe ever.

Sausage, Egg & Cheese Biscuit.name: Sausage, Egg & Cheese Biscuit
Sausage, Egg & Cheese Biscuit.description: Four words: Sausage. Egg. Cheese. Biscuit. Yeah, finally, you’ll want to eat your words. Because this buttermilk biscuit is topped with a freshly cracked egg, American cheese and sausage. Scratch that, it’s one word: Incredible.

Bacon, Egg & Cheese Biscuit.name: Bacon, Egg & Cheese Biscuit
Bacon, Egg & Cheese Biscuit.description: Four words: Bacon Egg. Cheese. Biscuit. Yeah, finally, you’ll want to eat your words. Because this buttermilk biscuit is topped with a freshly cracked egg, American cheese and bacon. Scratch that, it’s one word: Incredible.

Meat Lovers Burrito.name: Meat Lovers Burrito
Meat Lovers Burrito.description: Favorite fruit? Meat. Favorite veggie? Meat. Favorite burrito? This one. It’s got bacon, sausage, and ham—plus, scrambled eggs, pepper jack and cheddar cheese. And it’s all wrapped in a warm flour tortilla with a side of fire roasted salsa. Now that’s a food pyramid you can get behind.

Grande Sausage Burrito.name: Grande Sausage Burrito
Grande Sausage Burrito.description: Your mouth better do some push-ups. Because this is a whole lot of burrito with sausage, scrambled eggs, hash browns, bacon crumbles, and shredded pepper jack cheese. Plus, cheddar cheese sauce and creamy Sriracha sauce. And it’s all wrapped in a warm flour tortilla—with a side of fire roasted salsa. Phew. That was a workout just saying all of that.

Sausage Croissant.name: Sausage Croissant
Sausage Croissant.description: When Jack put sausage, a freshly cracked egg and American cheese on a buttery croissant, it earned the coveted title: “the sausage, freshly cracked egg and American cheese buttery croissant.” But that wouldn’t fit on the menu. Or anywhere. Hence, the shorthand.

Supreme Croissant.name: Supreme Croissant
Supreme Croissant.description: This breakfast croissant is more than good. Heck, it’s more than great. This flaky piece of heaven is supreme. Because it’s got grilled bacon, ham, a freshly cracked egg, and American cheese. And when you take a bite, you’re supreme, too. Those are the rules.

Club Salad.name: Club Salad
Club Salad.description: Grilled or crispy all-white meat chicken with shredded cheddar cheese, grape tomatoes, cucumbers, crumbled bacon and gourmet seasoned croutons on a blend of iceberg, romaine and spring lettuce with creamy ranch dressing

Grilled Chicken Salad.name: Grilled Chicken Salad
Grilled Chicken Salad.description: Elsewhere, a salad is an afterthought. But not here. Because this one has grilled all-white meat chicken, shredded cheddar cheese, grape tomatoes, cucumbers, carrots, gourmet seasoned croutons and low fat Balsamic dressing—all on a bed of iceberg, romaine, and spring lettuce. You won’t be able to get it out of your head. Or your mouth.

Southwest Salad.name: Southwest Salad
Southwest Salad.description: Pack your bags because you’re going southwest, my friend. To a salad made with a blend of iceberg, romaine, and spring lettuce. And your choice of grilled or crispy all-white meat chicken—along with shredded pepper jack cheese, roasted corn, grape tomatoes, black beans, spicy corn sticks and creamy southwest dressing. Actually, forget the bags. Pack a fork.

French Fries.name: French Fries
French Fries.description: Most French fries in the world don’t deserve their own description, but Jack’s do. Because these lightly salted, real potatoes are fried to crispy perfection and served hot and salty. They’re just that tasty.

Panko Onion Rings.name: Panko Onion Rings
Panko Onion Rings.description: True love is not an engagement ring. It’s an onion ring—panko breaded and fried to jaw-dropping perfection. But using an onion ring as an engagement ring? The judge will allow it. Just kidding. There’s not a judge for this type thing. Do whatever your stomach desires.

Stuffed Jalapeños.name: Stuffed Jalapeños
Stuffed Jalapeños.description: Where most see jalapeños, Jack sees opportunity. To bread ‘em and fill ‘em with melted cheeses. Yes, plural. And, if things get too hot, there’s tasty buttermilk ranch dipping sauce to cool down. Mmhmm. Jack’s got your back. And your stomach.

Egg Roll.name: Egg Roll
Egg Roll.description: It’s what’s on the inside that counts. That goes for you, sure. But it definitely goes for these crispy egg rolls—filled with diced pork, cabbage, celery, carrots, onions, and spices. But don’t forget the outside, where there’s sweet and sour dipping sauce. You can’t go wrong, really.

Seasoned Curly Fries.name: Seasoned Curly Fries
Seasoned Curly Fries.description: These Curly Fries are seasoned, alright. Seasoned veterans. They’ve been around the block—gathering deliciousness and flavor from all over. So, they know how to make your mouth water. And your tastebuds do their secret handshake.

Bacon Cheddar Potato Wedges.name: Bacon Cheddar Potato Wedges
Bacon Cheddar Potato Wedges.description: It doesn’t get any better than golden brown potato wedges. Well, unless you add melted cheddar cheese sauce, shredded cheddar cheese, and diced bacon bits. Which is exactly what we did. Microphone, consider yourself dropped.

Two Tacos.name: Two Tacos
Two Tacos.description: Sure, one is nice. But do you know what’s better? Two. Two crunchy tacos with American cheese, shredded lettuce, and taco sauce. Because two will always be greater than one. Who knew math could be so mouth-watering? Oh, right. We did.

Add Taco Sauce.name: Add Taco Sauce on the Side

Chicken Nuggets.name: Chicken Nuggets
Chicken Nuggets.description: One man’s all-white meat chicken nuggets are another man’s…well, nothing. Because that first man ate all of that crispy chicken amazingness. Next time, get your own, second man.

Chicken Sandwich.name: Chicken Sandwich
Chicken Sandwich.description: Chicken Sandwich, meet mouth. Mouth, meet Chicken Sandwich—made with a breaded chicken patty, real mayonnaise, and lettuce, all on a regular bun. You two will get along just fine. Just fine, indeed.

Extra Sauce.name: Add BBQ Sauce on the Side
Add Honey Mustard on the Side

Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger.name: Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger
Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger.description: You ever call something “junior,” ironically? Well, if you haven’t, you’re about to. Because this Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger is a 100% beef patty topped with hickory smoked bacon, American cheese, real mayonnaise and ketchup. And now you have a “junior” appetite. See what we did there?

Extra Sauce.name: Add BBQ Sauce on the Side
Add Honey Mustard on the Side

Jr. Jumbo Jack.name: Jr. Jumbo Jack
Jr. Jumbo Jack.description: Anywhere else this Jr. Jack would be senior. Because there is nothing junior about this honest-to-goodness beef patty topped with tomato, pickle, lettuce, and chopped onions—with the just-right amount of ketchup and real mayonnaise. But here? It’s got some growing up to do.

Extra Sauce.name: Add BBQ Sauce on the Side
Add Honey Mustard on the Side

Jumbo Jack.name: Jumbo Jack
Jumbo Jack.description: When you pick up the Jumbo Jack—made with a 100% beef patty topped with hand leafed lettuce, tomato, pickles, chopped onions, and real mayonnaise on a buttery bakery bun—your arms will tremble. And your mouth will open. It’s the delicious type of workout.

Extra Sauce.name: Add BBQ Sauce on the Side

Mini Churros (5pc).description: Topped with cinnamon and pure cane sugar

Cheesecake.name: Cheesecake
Cheesecake.description: The Big Apple has relocated to your mouth. And it’s not literally an apple. It’s a light and creamy cheesecake with a graham cracker crust. That’s way tastier than some over-rated piece of fruit.

Chocolate Overload Cake.name: Chocolate Overload Cake
Chocolate Overload Cake.description: If you’re looking for vanilla, you’ve made a wrong turn. Because this is a rich chocolate cake made with cocoa, bittersweet chocolate chips and then drizzled with chocolate buttercream icing. That’s some chocolatey chocolate chocolateness. That’s what that is.

FUZE® Tea.description: An adventurous blend of bold flavors where refreshing tea meets delicious fruit.

Zero Sugar FUZE® Tea.name: Zero Sugar FUZE® Tea
Zero Sugar FUZE® Tea.description: An adventurous blend of bold flavors where refreshing tea meets delicious fruit, with zero sugar.
